        "content": "<p>In the following example, the notation for <code>Formula.knows</code> gets unfolded in the infoview when doing <code>#check ğ•‚ Ï†</code>. <br>\nCan I make it so that the notation is preserved in the infoview, just like the prefix below for <code>Formula.negation</code>? <br>\nOr more generally, is there some customizability regarding what happens with notations when they are printed?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">inductive</span> <span class=\"n\">Formula</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">|</span> <span class=\"n\">negation</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Formula</span> <span class=\"bp\">â†’</span> <span class=\"n\">Formula</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">|</span> <span class=\"n\">knows</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Formula</span> <span class=\"bp\">â†’</span> <span class=\"n\">Formula</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">prefix</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">90</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"âˆ¼\"</span> <span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">Formula.negation</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">notation</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"ğ•‚\"</span> <span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">Formula.knows</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">variable</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Ï†</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Formula</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">#check</span> <span class=\"bp\">âˆ¼</span><span class=\"n\">Ï†</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">-- âˆ¼Ï† : Formula</span>\n<span class=\"k\">#check</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•‚</span> <span class=\"n\">Ï†</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">-- Formula.knows Ï† : Formula</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
